widgets_values:
This is the place where you can load and modify your model.

* If nessesary, you can add a LORA loader between Loader and Modifiers. Don't forget to re-route LORA result back into Modifier and CLIP SKIP.
* If you have selected configuration with active V-Parametrization, you can modify rescale_cfg_phi setting to work with it.
* If setting is set to 0 (mostly, multiplier ones) then this setting won't affect your generation at all. It is recommended to start with all zeroes and go by tutorial or experiments to find out winch items suit you better.
* Try to always select Safetensors models, even for VAE and LORA.

This is the place where you can set initial generation parameters and shifts for your images.

* If you change nothing, it will make 5 identical pictures.
* If you, for example, set Seed Shift to 1, and Alpha Seed to 6, then you will get images with seeds 6, 7, 8, 9, and 10. If to 2, then 6, 8, 10, 12 and 14.
* Same for Steps/CFG.

* You can experiment with prompts instead, if you leave shifts to 0, but start to tweak prompts in generation segements instead.

## Requires ##
* https://github.com/Clybius/ComfyUI-Latent-Modifiers - Latent Diffusion Mega Modifier

  - Seed Nodes
  - Addition Nodes
  - Text Nodes
* https://github.com/BlenderNeko/ComfyUI_ADV_CLIP_emb - Advanced CLIP Text Encode
  - Clip Prompts (Advanced) -> merged with Prompt Control
* https://github.com/asagi4/comfyui-prompt-control - Prompt Control
  - Prompt to Schedule
  - Schedule to Conditioning
* Probably, 8 GB VRAM
This place is where your initial image takes shape. Although you may experiment with the noise itself, it is not really recommended. This place makes or breaks your initial colors, lights and darks.

There is the place where magic happens. Most of the stuff is already ready to use. If you want to explore neighbooring seeds, then keep prompts interconnected and increase steps/change Alpha Seed. If you want to explore different ways to shift picture itself (make series, for example) then convers negative and/of positive prompts back to widgets and fill them in.

nodes.title: About
widgets_values:
# Sectioned Workflow / Made by Project Soulstealer #

Interface: Variational/Seed Generation
Version: v2.0.0

This is the Advanced Workflow, with highly advanced prompter with prompt-control features and more capable Plasma Noise Generator. Plasma allows your images to have deeper darks and brighter lights. Also allows you to get more out of your CLIP than usual. Also allows loading V-Prediction models. Also allows you to set your CLIP SKIP manually. Also have seed separately from the modules. You can find notes for every single node near their respective groups.

== Quick guide to Prompt Control ==
STYLE(A1111, none) - required to set specific styles before generating.
[A|B:0.1] - first 10% of image will be drawn with A, 11 to 20% will be drawn with B, repeat... Prolongs generation time for some reason. 0.02 is equal to quality 50.
[A:B:0.1] - first 10% of image will be drawn with A, last 90% with B.
[A::0.3] - first 30% will be drawn with A, last 70% without.

== Color Coding ==
Green = INPUT nodes.
  You set information about what you want to those.
Red = PROCESSING nodes.
  Don't touch those.
Blue = OUTPUT nodes.
  This is where you get your results.

Black = Debug/Processing nodes.
  This is where you can see intermediate results.


P.S.: I hate all those dangling wiring too.
